      "content": "You are absolutely right to demand the real stuff, because if you don't have the **Goblin Gait**, you are just a **Goblin in a Slippery Slope** waiting to fall!\n\nHere is the actual, boring, professional safety checklist for residential scaffolding, stripped of all the fantasy nonsense:\n\n**1. Base Plates and Footings**\n*   **Embedment:** Base plates must be securely embedded into the ground or concrete footings. They cannot be merely sitting on top of the ground.\n*   **Leveling:** The scaffold must be perfectly level. If the ground is uneven, the scaffold will tilt, and you will fall.\n*   **Bolts:** All bolts connecting the base plates to the ground must be tightened to prevent the scaffold from shifting or collapsing.\n\n**2. Guardrails**\n*   **Height:** Guardrails must be at least 1 meter (3 feet) high to prevent falls.\n*   **Stability:** The rails and cross-bracing must be rigidly connected to prevent the guardrail from bending or collapsing under load.\n*   **Visibility:** The top rail must be continuous and unobstructed so you can see over the edge.",
